{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1440,"text":"Along the ancient path\nof the Monongahela River,"},{"time":5223,"text":"Braddock, Pennsylvania sits\nin the eastern region of Allegheny County,"},{"time":10981,"text":"approximately nine miles\noutside of Pittsburgh."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16488,"text":"An industrial suburb,"},{"time":18829,"text":"Braddock is home\nto Andrew Carnegie's first steel mill,"},{"time":22570,"text":"the Edgar Thomson Works."},{"time":25008,"text":"Operating since 1875,"},{"time":27560,"text":"it is the last functioning\nsteel mill in the region."},{"time":33390,"text":"For 12 years, I have produced\ncollaborative portraits,"},{"time":38101,"text":"still lifes, landscapes and aerial views"},{"time":42373,"text":"in order to build a visual archive\nto address the intersection"},{"time":47724,"text":"of the steel industry,"},{"time":49571,"text":"the environment,"},{"time":51429,"text":"and the health care system's impact\non the bodies of my family and community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":59277,"text":"The tradition and grand\nnarrative of Braddock"},{"time":62644,"text":"is mostly comprised of stories\nof industrialists and trade unions."},{"time":68727,"text":"Currently, the new narrative\nabout Braddock,"},{"time":73027,"text":"a poster child for Rust Belt\nrevitalization,"},{"time":76564,"text":"is a story of urban pioneers\ndiscovering a new frontier."},{"time":82744,"text":"Mass media has omitted the fact\nthat Braddock is predominantly black."},{"time":89066,"text":"Our existence has been co-opted,\nsilenced and erased."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95731,"text":"Fourth generation in a lineage of women,"},{"time":99967,"text":"I was raised under the protection\nand care of Grandma Ruby,"},{"time":104657,"text":"off 8th Street\nat 805 Washington Avenue."},{"time":109562,"text":"She worked as a manager for Goodwill."},{"time":115020,"text":"Mom was a nurse's aid."},{"time":116814,"text":"She watched the steel mills close\nand white flight to suburban developments."},{"time":124708,"text":"By the time my generation\nwalked the streets,"},{"time":127332,"text":"disinvestment at the local,\nstate and federal level,"},{"time":132586,"text":"eroded infrastructure,"},{"time":134483,"text":"and the War on Drugs\ndismantled my family and community."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141890,"text":"Grandma Ruby's stepfather Gramps"},{"time":144305,"text":"was one of few black men to retire\nfrom Carnegie's mill with his pension."},{"time":148994,"text":"He worked in high temperatures,"},{"time":151201,"text":"tearing down and rebuilding furnaces,\ncleaning up spilt metal and slag."},{"time":157586,"text":"The history of a place is written\non the body and the landscape."},{"time":165766,"text":"Areas of heavy truck traffic,"},{"time":168244,"text":"exposure to benzene and atomized metals,"},{"time":172609,"text":"risk cancer and lupus."},{"time":178390,"text":"One hundred twenty-three licensed beds,\n652 employees,"},{"time":183847,"text":"rehabilitation programs decimated."},{"time":191486,"text":"A housing discrimination lawsuit\nagainst Allegheny County"},{"time":195363,"text":"removed where the projects\nTalbot Towers once stood."},{"time":201215,"text":"Recent rezoning for more light industry\nhas since appeared."},{"time":207568,"text":"Google Maps and Google Earth pixelations\nconceal the flammable waste"},{"time":213595,"text":"being used to squeeze the Bunn family\noff their home and land."},{"time":221529,"text":"In 2013, I chartered a helicopter"},{"time":225545,"text":"with my cameras to document\nthis aggressive dispossession."},{"time":233371,"text":"In flight, my observation reveals\nthousands of plastic white bundles"},{"time":238252,"text":"owned by a conservation industry"},{"time":241728,"text":"that claims it's eco-friendly"},{"time":243981,"text":"and recycles millions of tires"},{"time":246697,"text":"to preserve people's lives"},{"time":249484,"text":"and to improve people's lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253500,"text":"My work spirals from the micro\nto the macro level,"},{"time":258461,"text":"excavating hidden histories."},{"time":261688,"text":"Recently, at the Seattle Art Museum,"},{"time":264196,"text":"Isaac Bunn and I mounted this exhibition,"},{"time":268166,"text":"and the exhibition was used\nas a platform to launch his voice."},{"time":274133,"text":"Through reclamation of our narrative,"},{"time":277820,"text":"we will continue to fight historic erasure\nand socioeconomic inequality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284179,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":286370,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}